folder: Spring Street & Varick Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Spring Street at,and adjoining and East of the South East corner of Varick Street. To and including 240 Spring Street,a little faced frame house. 256-254 Spring Street,the houses at and adjoining the South East corner of Varick Street were demolished in 1914 or 1915,when Varick St. was widened it's entire length at the expense of the East Side,during the construction of the West Side Interborough Line.
The church is the Spring Street Presbyterian Church,which was built on that site in 1811,and in it's present form since 1835.

P.L.Sperr,                     NEG.# 4187
                             May 12th,1927

(2)
The same. The Presbyterian Church on the South Side of Spring St.

P.L.Sperr,

folder: Spring Street & Varick Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Spring Street Presbyterian Church, adjoining the S.E. corner of Varick Street. This edifice was built in 1835, on the site of the original Spring Street Church, which was built here in 1811 of material from the old First Church in Wall Street. This print, of course, fails to show the color of the church, the walls of which are a sort of salmon pink.
June 23, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
